Brock Guzman was taken from his home in Fairfield, California on Monday morning as he slept in the family car . 
  His parents Paul and Suzanne are now filing a complaint against police for the way they treated them after they reported their son missing . 
  Paul claims his wife Suzanne was handcuffed and thrown to the ground by officers after she refused to let them into their home . 
  Brock was found in the car just hours after he was stolen . 
  Paul says he left Brock in the vehicle while he went inside to grab something . 
  The car was stolen from their driveway at around 4:45am on Monday . 
  He claims he reported his son missing because his wife was refusing to let police into the home . 
 